## Current Repo Fit

- Formula orchestration already lives in `gastown/beads/formulas/README.md`.
- Existing production formulas already use `pour = true`, including:
  - `gastown/beads/formulas/draft-spec-expansion.formula.toml`
  - `gastown/beads/formulas/enrich-expansion.formula.toml`
  - `gastown/beads/formulas/beadify-expansion.formula.toml`
  - `gastown/beads/formulas/spec-to-beads-workflow.formula.toml`
  - `gastown/beads/formulas/single-session-tracking-workflow.formula.toml`
- Specs are already the canonical artifact via `gastown/docs/templates/spec.md`.
- Session continuity already exists through:
  - multi-session checkpoints in `gastown/beads/formulas/spec-to-beads-workflow.formula.toml`
  - single-session artifacts in `gastown/beads/formulas/single-session-tracking-workflow.formula.toml`
- The local `gastown/skills/brainstorming/SKILL.md` is explicitly adapted from `obra/superpowers`.

## Existing Entry Points and Patterns

- Expansion formulas use `type = "expansion"` with `[[template]]`.
- Workflow formulas use `type = "workflow"` with `[[steps]]` and compose/expand behavior.
- Current commands already cover a large part of the intended flow:
  - `gt sling draft-spec-expansion`
  - `gt sling enrich-expansion`
  - `gt sling beadify-expansion`
  - `gt sling spec-to-beads-workflow`
  - `gt sling single-session-tracking-workflow`
- Execution is molecule-based, using `bd mol current` and `bd close` to progress steps.

## Superpowers Concepts Worth Mapping

- `hooks/session-start` and `.opencode/plugins/superpowers.js` implement strong session priming by injecting `using-superpowers`.
- `skills/using-superpowers/SKILL.md` enforces an early skill-selection gate before normal interaction.
- The main upstream workflow chain is effectively:
  - brainstorming
  - using-git-worktrees
  - writing-plans
  - either subagent-driven-development or executing-plans
  - requesting-code-review
  - finishing-a-development-branch
- `skills/subagent-driven-development/SKILL.md` defines an explicit reviewer loop:
  - implementer
  - spec reviewer
  - code-quality reviewer
  - repeat if needed
  - final implementation review
- `skills/test-driven-development/SKILL.md` provides the clearest gap versus Gastown:
  - red test first
  - prove failure
  - minimal green implementation
  - refactor while green

## Best Formula Opportunity

- A new formula appears most valuable if it collapses superpowers-style orchestration into a single Gastown workflow rather than replacing the current spec pipeline wholesale.
- The best candidate is a workflow with:
  - a session-priming or workflow-selection gate
  - phase routing across brainstorm/spec/implementation
  - an explicit execution mode branch
  - review-order constraints
  - stronger test-first verification

## Key Gap vs Today

- Gastown already has `pour=true`, spec generation, session tracking, and workflow composition.
- The biggest missing capability is a first-class test-driven loop with enforced sequencing and proof artifacts, rather than only post-hoc verification commands and spec-derived testing notes.
